(231, 'Thripunithura', 'Cochin', 1, 5000, 'March - June', 'South', 'Adventure', 'The Hill Palace, Kerala''s first heritage museum noted for royal collections of the erstwhile Maharaja of Kochi, is today the largest archaeological museum in Kerala. Built in 1865, the palace complex consists of 49 buildings in the trational architectural style of Kerala, sprawled over 52 acres of beautifully landscaped terraced land which houses a deer park and facilities for horse riding. Numerous species of flora including rare medicinal plants grow here. ', 'Hotel Anil Vikas,Kundannur junction,Thrippunithara', 'Bus', 3, 'Thripunithura.jpg'),
